Review: I so could have watched another hour of this—a world you just never want to leave. Miyazaki is a literal gift to this planet and I still kind of can't believe we got to experience a new film of his in theatres. Without a doubt a cinema-going event I will never forget !!!!

Emerald Fennell you nasty as hell but I’m not complaining. STUPIDLY gorgeous cinematography (4:3 used so well here MWAH), stylish montages, linen, cigarettes, obsession, HOT people and a whole lot of fucked up pervertedness. A great time naturally

The return of the (Paul) King…except this time he’s stuck with a somewhat unconvincing lead performance and a mostly dud script/musical numbers. When it works, it’s magical though. King’s style shines through even though it’s a big step down quality wise from the Paddington films

Movie: The Hunger Games: The Ballad of Songbirds & Snakes
Review: I didn’t pay to see this and I still feel like I wasted my money

I wish the CREATOR of this SCRIPT (ily Gareth Edwards) hand-balled it to someone else where ✨CHARACTER DEVELOPMENT✨ and ✨BETTER WRITING✨ was a thing. It’s hard not to be disappointed by how this turned out. The direction is strong and the technical elements impress…I liked the through-line of the story however simple it is…BUT THE SCREENPLAY and CHARACTERISATION. Oof. It’s a film all about love and emotion but it’s severely lacking in both. The central heart of the story didn’t…

Brian Duffield you fucking rock honestly. So many of these visuals are gonna stick with me for a very long time. But once fucking again shame on Disney for not putting this in theatres..depressing to think this could disappear into thin air like their other Disney+/Hulu releases :/
The vibes were immaculate but my dumb ass couldn’t understand 95% of this ngl

Sooo it’s giving temu original and it’s often not very well written/directed/performed…BUT it’s so extremely charming and the first half is swoon town central. Does take quite a nose dive in the latter half sadly that it never really recovers from. Still gonna take it as a w for the gays tho

I am the least patriotic person on the planet..but it does fill me with a slight sense of pride when a really great Australian film comes along and blows up in way that’s deserved. Such a crazy strong debut from two filmmakers who without question have a long and exciting career ahead of them

WELL! There is so much I am still trying to process and unpack here that my brain feels like it's about to explode. I don’t think I’ve ever said “oh my god” out loud in the cinema that many times before??? A deranged fever dream on crippling anxiety and generational trauma- directed by a man with a LONG overdue trip to the therapist. I was sitting in total awe of everything I saw during the first act of this. It's…
Maika Monroe out here constantly finding bold and creative projects to star in and it’s just further proof that it’s her world and we’re all just living in it
